nodes.bodyText:
If you want to avoid the let you could use fp.cond, returning an object and destructuring out the variables.
Something like:
const {presetDiskSize, presetMachineName} = fp.cond([
  [() => !!runtimeTemplate.gceConfig, ({gceConfig: {bootDiskSize, machineType}}) =>({
    presetDiskSize: bootDiskSize,
    presetMachineName: machineType
  })],
  [() => !!runtimeTemplate.dataprocConfig, ...]
])(runtimeTemplate)
The above example uses on some additional destructuring in the map function signature

